* 1 _The project information I chose to document_
- I chose to document is the `JavaScript Task Manager`. The project is a modular command-line task management application built with JavaScript and Node.js. It provides functionality for creating, organizing, prioritizing, tracking, and synchronizing tasks using a persistent JSON-based storage system.

  The application follows a layered architecture with separate modules for:
  Task data modeling
  Business logic and task management
  Persistent storage
  Command-line interaction
  Task parsing and prioritization utilities
  Task synchronization and conflict resolution
  The system is designed to be lightweight, extensible, and easy to maintain.

