@code markdown

# Task Manager — Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)

This FAQ is designed for beginners who may be new to command-line applications.

It explains:

* How to get started
* How to know if commands worked
* Common task management operations
* How to troubleshoot errors
* How to tell the difference between user mistakes and program issues

---

# Getting Started

## What is Task Manager?

Task Manager is a command-line application that helps you:

* Create tasks
* Organize work
* Set priorities
* Add due dates
* Track progress
* Save tasks permanently

Tasks are stored locally on your computer in a file called:

```text id="c99uqz"
tasks.json
```

---

## Do I need programming experience to use this application?

No.

You only need:

* Basic computer skills
* A terminal or command prompt
* Node.js installed

The commands are simple and beginner-friendly.

---

## What is a command line?

The command line (also called a terminal or command prompt) is a text-based interface where you type commands.

Examples:

### Windows

* Command Prompt
* PowerShell

### macOS/Linux

* Terminal

---

## How do I start the application?

Open your terminal inside the project folder and run:

```bash id="x7mryx"
node cli.js
```

To see available commands:

```bash id="n93f7m"
node cli.js --help
```

---

## How do I know if the application is working?

If the application is working correctly, you will see:

* A help menu
* A success message
* A list of tasks
* Or command output

Example:

```text id="u7wgdl"
Created task with ID: 4f8a12bc
```

This means the command succeeded.

---

# Creating Tasks

## How do I create a task?

Run:

```bash id="8zofm4"
node cli.js create "Buy groceries"
```

Example successful output:

```text id="06l0wc"
Created task with ID: a1b2c3d4
```

---

## How do I know if the task was actually created?

After creating a task, run:

```bash id="5ksahh"
node cli.js list
```

If the task appears in the list, it was successfully saved.

Example:

```text id="rmvz6u"
[ ] a1b2c3d4 - !! Buy groceries
```

---

## Can I add more details when creating a task?

Yes.

Example:

```bash id="o3k48r"
node cli.js create "Finish report" --priority 4 --due 2026-06-01 --tags work,urgent
```

---

## What do the priority numbers mean?

| Number | Priority |
| ------ | -------- |
| 1      | Low      |
| 2      | Medium   |
| 3      | High     |
| 4      | Urgent   |

---

## What happens if I enter an invalid date?

Example invalid command:

```bash id="2iz9gi"
node cli.js create "Test" --due tomorrowish
```

You may see:

```text id="b2t5p4"
Invalid date format. Use YYYY-MM-DD
```

This is usually a user input error, not a program failure.

Correct format:

```text id="9zwm6g"
2026-05-28
```

---

# Viewing and Managing Tasks

## How do I view all tasks?

Run:

```bash id="w68aef"
node cli.js list
```

---

## How do I view a specific task?

Run:

```bash id="7yg0eo"
node cli.js show <task_id>
```

Example:

```bash id="1oj1u4"
node cli.js show a1b2c3d4
```

---

## How do I know if a task exists?

Use:

```bash id="3d4wdr"
node cli.js list
```

or:

```bash id="x78l4z"
node cli.js show <task_id>
```

If the task exists, its details will appear.

If not, you will see:

```text id="e4k3dc"
Task not found.
```

---

# Marking Tasks Complete

## How do I mark a task as completed?

Run:

```bash id="db8uy0"
node cli.js status <task_id> done
```

Example:

```bash id="ywqxxp"
node cli.js status a1b2c3d4 done
```

Success message:

```text id="spbq0g"
Updated task status to done
```

